        "_account_id": 805,
        "name": "Neil Brown",
        "email": "neil@brown.name",
        "username": "neilbrown"
      },
      "date": "2020-11-30 02:57:00.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nIt's a bit sad that is several of these cases the \"name\" string is the result of an earlier sprintf() call.  I think it would be cleaner to call kthread_run() at the point where that first sprintf happens.\nThe wrapper this just increments a counter could be open-coded and discarded.\n\nOr maybe var-args could be passed to the wrapper, but I'm not sure that is worth it.\n\nSo: I wouldn't \"fix\" it like this, but that patch doesn't make anything worse...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
